        <abstract>
            <p>Remembers JDH’s encouragement when he was "utterly weary of life".</p>
            <p>Marvellous about European forms in Fernando Po.</p> 
<p>C. V. Naudin will publish a book on hybridity ["Nouvelles recherches sur l’hybridité dans les végétaux", <hi rend="italic">Nouv. Arch. Mus. Hist. Nat. Paris</hi> 1 (1865): 25–176; part also in <hi rend="italic">Ann. Sci. Nat. (Bot.)</hi> (1863)].</p> 
            <p>CD fears Naudin has underestimated distribution of pollen by insects.</p>
            <p>Melastomatous plants are ready for his work on meaning of two sets of anthers.</p> 
<p>Very curious about <hi rend="italic">Masdevallia</hi>.</p> 
            <p>George [Darwin] observing orchids.</p> 
<p>Adaptation of <hi rend="italic">Herminium</hi> beats almost every other orchid.</p> 
        </abstract>
